headline: Why Analysts Think IBM’s Story Is Shifting As Quantum Hopes Lift Fair Value
summary: International Business Machines is seeing a quiet but meaningful reset in its narrative, as our fair value estimate edges up from about $287.09 to $290.89 per share alongside a slight lift in assumed revenue growth from roughly 5.14% to 5.16% annually. These tweaks reflect increasing confidence that IBM's growing quantum and automation businesses can more than offset lingering questions around core software momentum. Read on to see how these evolving assumptions can help you stay informed...
